data: ─── SCENE

data:  ───

The ash in the hearth of Tremaine Manor never truly cools. For Ella, it is a second

data:  skin, a grey shroud that marks her as a ghost in her own home. While her stepsisters, Anastasia and Drizella,

data:  tighten their corsets until their breath comes in shallow gasps, Ella kneels in the soot, scouring the silver that

data:  will never be hers. The manor is a skeleton of its former glory, its tapestries moth-eaten and its wine

data:  cellars dry, held together only by the iron will of Lady Tremaine and the debt she owes to the Crown.

A

data:  heavy iron knock shudders through the oak front door. The Royal Herald doesn't bring a mere invitation; he brings a command

data: . The "Reclamation Ball" is to be held in three days’ time. The King’s health is failing

data: , and the Prince—a man rumored to be as cold as the marble halls he inhabits—must find a match

data:  to stabilize a kingdom on the brink of civil unrest. This is not a fairy tale; it is a political auction, and the

data:  daughters of the nobility are the currency.

Lady Tremaine’s eyes, sharp as flint, settle on Ella as

data:  the scroll is unrolled. She doesn't see a daughter or even a servant; she sees a complication. The invitation explicitly

data:  demands the presence of "all daughters of the blood" of the Great Houses. Ella is the only one who truly carries the Trem

data: aine lineage, her father’s blood running through her veins, while her stepsisters are merely shadows brought in after the

data:  fact. If Ella attends, she is the rightful heir to the estate—and the greatest threat to her stepmother’s survival

data: .

[REVEAL: The invitation is stamped with a black seal, signifying that this ball is also a trial of

data:  lineage where the "unworthy" may not return.]

─── STAKES ───
THREAT — Lady Tremaine may

data:  resort to permanent measures to ensure Ella cannot claim her inheritance.
OPPORTUNITY — The palace holds the archives that could prove

data:  how Ella’s father truly died.
UNKNOWN — The Prince’s "coldness" is whispered to be a cover

data:  for a brewing coup within the castle walls.

─── CHOICES ───
A. **Demand your birth

data: right.** Confront Lady Tremaine openly and insist on attending as the head of the house.
B. **Work from the shadows

data: .** Agree to stay behind, but secretively plot to infiltrate the ball as a masked "nobody."
C. **Seek the

data:  Forbidden.** Venture into the Whispering Woods to find the "Old Woman"—a disgraced alchemist who owed your father a

data:  life-debt.
D. **Burn the lineage.** Destroy the documents proving your noble blood to escape the lethal politics

data:  of the court forever.

─── RESOLUTION ───
This is the beginning.
RESOLVED — The

data:  Call to Court: The royal invitation has arrived, setting the gears of fate in motion.
OPEN — The Inheritance: Lady

data:  Tremaine’s hold on the manor is fragile, and Ella’s very existence threatens it.

